		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I like IDA, too. But, all I have is the free version. I don't have the Do'H! to get the full version.
<br />
<br />As far as the code/data sep, I just follow the code through the reset, nmi &amp; irq_brk vectors. I have an interactive jump table builder in there, too - i.e, you give the start address and num of entries.
<br />
<br />I will look into the .cdl file right now - that may be a great feature.
<br />
<br />About mappers &amp; disasm, if I am thinking right, say the game megaman.nes was loaded. it has 26 code blocks, and uses mapper 2 (UNROM).  the last block in this rom loads at C000. All of the other blocks would have an org of $8000, correct?
<br />
<br />thanks,

		

